The claim with the title 'Promise check: delay superannuation increase by two years ' says When the Coalition announced its small business policy on august 19, 2013 one of its key promises was to "defer by two years the increase in compulsory employer-funded superannuation". At his campaign launch speech on august 25, Tony Abbott said: "we'll delay the superannuation guarantee levy increase because it's another cost that small business can't afford right now." 
